column4: Added fitness tracker - a CSV file is no generated which contains the average fitness of each population over time. I also plan to add Q1-Q4 as well as variance.

Began creating a new GUI using the G4P library and associated GUI builder, this makes it much easier to add new elements easily as I don't have to worry about the specifics of the GUI. I have also made a few more adjustments to the breeding, notably mutation now only happen to random synapses, rather than mutation randomly happening to every synapse. Changed the running boolean (the toggle between to config menu and the actual running of the simulation to a state value which would make it easier to add other states (e.g, viewing fitness/time graphs) in the future.
More cleaning, researched some GUI builders, added/fixed some comments...
Fixed up multithreading to use the Java class, need to do some more cleaning up of code though
Setup proper Java multithreading and IT WORKED FIRST TRY There's an inconsistent glitch which crashes at the noise function with a divide by 0 error so I'll need to fix that, maybe at a sleep
More gradual improvements. Adjusted some stuff, trying to find the best way to implement javax.swing.
Sorted out the inputs, current glitch: the FOV lines aren't accurate.
Added breeding and multiples games... among MANY other things. It now technically works! (fixed bullets(
